    "project_template_level_name": "ai-generated-design-lesson8-level4-template-test-2025",
    "long_instructions": "##Apply Accessibility Principles to Your Own App\r\n- Choose one of the following **personas with an accessibility constraint**:\r\n    - **User A**: Low vision → may struggle with color contrast.\r\n    - **User B**: Motor difficulty → may need larger buttons or simplified navigation.\r\n    - **User C**: Screen reader use → needs alt text and semantic headings.\r\n- Inspect your own app/page using **POUR framework** to identify at least 2–3 accessibility issues.\r\n- Use the **Accessibility Prompt Builder** (in your Activity Guide) to draft AI prompts for fixes.\r\n- Document issues identified and the AI prompts drafted to fix them and save to **Backpack**\r\n",
